main event: A round, orange and red object was observed at an altitude of approximately 40,000 feet over Cartersville, Virginia on August 6, 1956.
interesting points: The object was first brought to the observer's attention by a 'flash through the trees'.
The object had no movement and was observed for 45 seconds.
The report states 'insufficient data for evaluation'.
The object was observed by a civilian witness.
The report includes handwritten details and a teletype-style message.
sighted object: a round, orange and red object
